  "remote_port": 443,
  "prompt": "I have forgotten ssc cgl password, what should I do now?",
  "response": "I'm sorry to hear that you've forgotten your SSC CGL (Staff Selection Commission Combined Graduate Level) password. Don't worry\u2014this is a common issue, and you can easily reset your password by following these steps:\n\n### **Step-by-Step Guide to Reset Your SSC CGL Password**\n\n1. **Visit the Official SSC Website:**\n   - Go to the official SSC portal: [https://ssc.nic.in/](https://ssc.nic.in/)\n   \n2. **Navigate to the Login Page:**\n   - Click on the \"Login\" button typically located at the top-right corner of the homepage.\n\n3. **Select the Appropriate Login Option:**\n   - Choose the relevant login category (e.g., Candidate Login) based on your requirement.\n\n4. **Click on \"Forgot Password\":**\n   - On the login page, locate and click the \"Forgot Password\" link. This option is usually found below the password field.\n\n5. **Enter Required Details:**\n   - You will be prompted to enter specific details to verify your identity. This may include:\n     - **User ID/Enrollment Number/Application Number:** Enter the ID you used during registration.\n     - **Registered Email Address:** Ensure you have access to this email, as the reset link will be sent here.\n     - **Security Verification:** Complete any CAPTCHA or security checks displayed.\n\n6. **Submit the Request:**\n   - After entering the required information, click on the \"Submit\" or \"Send Password\" button.\n\n7. **Check Your Email:**\n   - Open your registered email account and look for an email from SSC containing the password reset link.\n   - **Note:** Check your spam or junk folder if you don't see the email in your inbox.\n\n8. **Reset Your Password:**\n   - Click on the password reset link provided in the email.\n   - You'll be redirected to a page where you can set a new password.\n   - **Choose a Strong Password:** Use a combination of letters, numbers, and special characters to ensure security.\n   - Confirm the new password by entering it again.\n\n9. **Login with New Credentials:**\n   - Return to the SSC login page and enter your User ID and the newly set password to access your account.\n\n### **Additional Tips:**\n\n- **Keep Your Details Handy:** Ensure you have your registration details like User ID, Enrollment Number, or Application Number ready before initiating the password reset process.\n  \n- **Use a Valid Email Address:** Make sure the email address registered with SSC is active and accessible. If you've lost access to your registered email, you may need to contact SSC support for further assistance.\n\n- **Clear Browser Cache:** If you're experiencing issues with password reset links not working, try clearing your browser's cache or using a different browser.\n\n- **Contact SSC Helpdesk:**\n  - If the above steps don't resolve your issue, consider reaching out to the SSC helpdesk:\n    - **Email:** You can send an email detailing your problem to the official SSC email address (usually found on the SSC contact page).\n    - **Phone:** Call the SSC helpline number provided on the website for immediate assistance.\n    - **Address:** Visit the nearest SSC regional office if you require in-person help.\n\n### **Preventive Measures for the Future:**\n\n- **Use a Password Manager:** To avoid forgetting your passwords, consider using a reliable password manager to store and manage your login credentials securely.\n  \n- **Regularly Update Passwords:** Change your passwords periodically to enhance security.\n\n- **Note Down Credentials Safely:** Keep a secure record of your important login details in a safe place.\n\nI hope this helps you regain access to your SSC CGL account smoothly. If you encounter any specific issues during the process, feel free to provide more details, and I can assist you further!",
